{
  "doc_id": "55097",
  "text": "Office BP was calculated as the average of the last two of three measurements of SBP and DBP, made with a validated sphygmomanometer (OMRON Model M10-IT). Measurements were made on the dominant arm while participants were in a seated position after at least five minutes, with a cuff of appropriate size as determined by measurement of the upper arm circumference and following the recommendations of the European Society of Hypertension [CITATION_1] . Mean arterial pressure (MAP) was calculated as the sum of the SBP and twice the DBP, divided by three.",
  "correct_citation": {
